Russia
on Thursday expanded an entry ban on U.S. officials to include U.S.
Vice-President Kamala Harris and 28 other American officials, businesspeople
and journalists. The
sanctions list, published by the Russian foreign ministry, included Facebook
founder Mark Zuckerberg, Deputy Defence Secretary Kathleen Hicks and Pentagon
spokesperson John Kirby, among others  "These individuals are denied entry into the Russian
Federation indefinitely," the Russian foreign ministry said in a statement.